profile.primary_concern: accessing PrEP while living in a shelter

context: Living in a shelter can create significant barriers to accessing healthcare services, including PrEP. The individual may feel anxious about stigma related to their living situation and fear that it will affect their ability to receive proper healthcare. They may be hopeful for better health but unsure of how to navigate the system.
